  "summary": {
    "macroSummary": "Markets are rallying strongly on hopes of a US-Iran peace deal that could normalize Hormuz Strait traffic, with stocks hitting records and oil plunging as geopolitical tensions ease. Bitcoin and crypto are benefiting from the risk-on sentiment with nearly $1B in weekly BTC ETF inflows, though underlying metrics show some caution with miner selling and low trading volumes suggesting this may be more relief rally than sustainable trend reversal.",
    "regimeImpact": "The peace deal optimism and oil decline supports the oversold relief rally thesis, but we remain in the bear market regime until SPY decisively breaks above 662 and sustains.",
    "actionItems": [
      "Monitor BMNR ladder strikes closely as BTC approaches $77k resistance - consider rolling up if we break above $76.5k with conviction",
      "Reduce short book exposure temporarily given peace deal momentum, but maintain core positions as relief rallies can reverse quickly",
      "Add to Maturity sector overweight on any pullback as defensive positioning remains prudent in bear market regime"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "Oil plunging on Hormuz normalization hopes removes stagflation pressure and supports risk assets short-term.",
      "Bitcoin ETF inflows of nearly $1B weekly show institutional demand returning but miner selling suggests supply pressure building.",
      "Polymarket odds of 73% for Hormuz normalization by May-end indicates market pricing in geopolitical resolution.",
      "Trump's Iran nuclear stance and upcoming US-Iran talks next week represent binary catalyst that could extend or reverse relief rally."
    ]
